Lady Si'neela has soft, golden-brown skin yet it appears fragile.

She also appears to be young but a closer look reveals worry lines upon her forehead. Her eyes are dark and mysterious and she seems to be constantly looking upon you.

She wears a white and cream colored gown that gleams beautifully against the temple candlelight. Her raven-black hair blows in the desert zephyr that gusts in from the temple entrance when you enter.

She has impeccable manners that mark her as a noble amongst the village people and her gait is stately. She's also well-groomed and indeed from the looks of it she's a priestess of Lathander. 

Her presence instills a sense of calm, peace and tranquility; however there is a mysterious aura that dwells about her, although you know somehow that she is of good intent.

This ragged soldier has a relaxed peaceful stance as he stands in duty for his Temple.  It is obvious he has been here for a long time, as he seems extremely confident in his position, as well as battle-worn and ready. His skin is dark and weathered by exposure to the sun and sand and his frayed tunic shows signs of bleaching, the gold of the uniform having faded to a brownish yellow.
Man-at-arms of the Church of the Morninglord

value.0: A prim and proper, steadfast cleric of Torm and just recently of Lathander as well.
A book in the hand is worth two on the shelf!
An austere priest with sharp eyes, Yarma keeps an eye out for adventurers who may be looking for work.

Value.value: Hello, if you are are looking for something to do, we are in need of help.
To the south of here, east of the Hasrabet waystation, is a small pass that leads you to a set of cliffs and passes belonging to a tribe of minotaurs.
They often raid carvans going through and are known to steal goods from them.
Ah, I see you found something. I will take this to return to its rightful owner. Thank you, and here is your reward.
When you reach Hasrabet, you can find the minotaurs through a cliff entrance. We have it blocked to normal travel, but you should be able to climb over the posts.
Thank you for aiding us. *dips his head*
If you could find out where they take them, and bring back any stolen objects, that would be a great help to us.
Bring them back to me at the Temple, and I'll handle getting them back to their owners.

value.0: Detailed carvings cover the surface of this finely-crafted door. The handiwork is of high quality and no doubt came at quite an expense.

Lathander's Dogma: Strive always to aid, to foster new hope, new ideas and new prosperity for all humankind and its allies. It is a sacred duty to foster new growth, nurture growing things, and work for rebirth and renewal. Perfect yourself, and be fertile in mind and body. Wherever you go, plant seeds of hope, new ideas, and plans for a rosy future in the minds of all. Watch each sunrise. Consider the consequences of your actions so that your least effort may bring the greatest and best reward. Avoid negativity, for from death comes life, and there is always another morning to turn a setback into a success. Place more importance in activities that help others than in strict adherence to rules, rituals, and the dictates of your seniors.
